HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 364
BY REPRESENTATIVE FREEMAN
A RESOLUTION
To express the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death of Sharon
Courtney and to honor her life, legacy, and contributions to the political landscape
of the city of New Orleans and the state of Louisiana.
WHEREAS, it is with profound sorrow that the Louisiana House of Representatives
has learned of the passing of Sharon Courtney on May 21, 2026, after a brief and courageous
battle with colon cancer; and
WHEREAS, Sharon was born in 1965 in Aberdeen, Mississippi, and graduated from
the University of Mississippi in 1987 with a degree in journalism; and
WHEREAS, Sharon moved to Washington, D.C., and began a thirty-eight-year
government relations career as a legislative assistant on Capitol Hill; she started in the office
of Congressman Larkin Smith and then served in the office of Congressman John Murtha,
where she spent five and a half years focusing on health care and education issues; and
WHEREAS, Sharon moved to New Orleans in 1994 and resided in the city for
thirty-two years; and
WHEREAS, Sharon brought her valuable experience on Capitol Hill to Tulane
University, where she spent over thirty years as a leader in community and government
relations; and
